This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with attributed networks, which are a type of social network with auxiliary attribute information. Additionally, the paper focuses on network downstream tasks such as link prediction and node classification, which are common in social network analysis. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques for learning node embeddings, which suggests that it could belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

Furthermore, the paper involves the reconstruction of a denser network, which could fall under the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.SD (Software Engineering). 

The paper also involves parameter sensitivity analysis, which suggests that it could belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as these fields often involve parameter tuning and analysis.
